<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornado Kills Over 60 People Killed in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- At least over 60 people were
killed and 1,000 others injured when a severe cyclone ripped
through some areas in India's West Bengal and Orissa states
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that at least 50 people were killed
and over 1,000 injured in a big tornado in West Bengal's Midnapore
district bordering Orissa state. The toll might rise as the rescue
operation was in full swing.
</P>
<P>
At least 16 people were killed and several others injured when
a tornado hit some villages in Jaleswar of Balasore district in
Orissa state Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
All the 16 bodies were brought to the Jaleswar primary health
center and the casualty figure was likely to go up.
</P>
<P>
Senior district officers rushed to the spot to undertake rescue
and relief measures, which were hampered following torrential
rains in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
