<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 36.14 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 36.14 points to
3927.67 as against Monday's close of 3963.81.
</P>
<P>
The national index also downed by 12.72 points to 1709.48 as
against the previous close of 1722.20.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted down at 378.87
and 159.53 compared with Monday's close of 381.12 and 160.60
respectively.
</P>
<P>
After an initial buoyancy, equities later met with resistance
and fell back partially, bringing down the sensitive index by over
36 points on the stock market Tuesday due to profit-taking by
operators and financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The market was expected to start on a better note Wednesday
followed by another correction after the midsession, a dealer
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
