<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Prime Minister to Attend Asia-Europe Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai said Monday that he will attend the second Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM) in London early next month.
</P>
<P>
Khai told Xinhua that he and his delegation will study how to
effectively cooperate with other countries, especially in economic
development, at the ASEM.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister will go on to visit to Belgium and hold talks
with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
He described his upcoming visits to Western Europe as important
and hoped that the cooperative ties between Vietnam and the
European Union would be further developed. 
