<HEADLINE> Denmark to Continue to Practise Tight Fiscal Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 24 (Xinhua)-- Danish Prime Minister Poul Nyrup
Rasmussen said Monday that his new cabinet will continue its tight
fiscal policy, lower corporate tax and promote cooperation in the
Baltic Sea Region.
</P>
<P>
The Social Democratic-led government's targets are low
inflation, stable patterns of private saving, an increased surplus
in the state budget as well as in the balance of trade.
</P>
<P>
The Danish press have suggested that the fiscal and monetary
policies will be forced to meet the demands of the European
Monetary Union despite the fact that Denmark, like Sweden, will
not be among the first to adopt the single European currency.
</P>
</TEXT>
