<HEADLINE> Ung Huot Welcomes Decision to Pardon Prince Ranariddh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's First Prime
Minister Ung Huot Tuesday welcomed a decision by King Norodom
Sihanouk to pardon Prince Norodom Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the king, Ung Huot said he welcomed the decision
to completely pardon Ranariddh and also supported Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen's letter to the King to request the pardon.
</P>
<P>
He praised the continued efforts by the King to promote
democratic reconciliation, the state's independence, peace and
development. It is the pride of our nation, Ung Huot said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the pardon had removed all obstacles blocking
Ranariddh from participating the forthcoming general election in
July.
</P>
<P>
The pardon is in line with the common aspirations of the
people, that is to achieve the independence, peace, freedom,
democracy and development, Ung Huot said.
</P>
<P>
The King granted the pardon after receiving a direct appeal
from Second Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
The Prince announced Monday that he decided to return to
Cambodia on March 30, 1998. 
