<HEADLINE> Simitis: Greeks Determined to Build Strong Nation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Greek people today were using
their fortitude, vitality and fighting spirit to build a
contemporary and strong nation in order to successfully and
efficiently meet the challenges of the 21st century, Greek Prime
Minister Costas Simitis said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a message on Wednesday's 177th anniversary of the March
25,1821 declaration of the Greek war of independence against
Ottoman rule, Simitis said that today's Greeks were waging the
battle for Greece to have "a presence and voice" and to
participate equally and actively in the decision-making center of
the European Union.
</P>
<P>
He said that they were fighting for a Greece that guaranteed
economic stability and development with its national currency,
drachma, entered in the EU's exchange rate mechanism (ERM), and
ensured the competitiveness of its economy in the public and
private sectors through consolidation of the efficiency of public
organizations and utilities by providing qualitatively upgraded
services and facilitating the endeavors of Greek private
enterprises with prestige and presence on the international
markets.
</P>
<P>
The Greeks, he continued, were building a Greece with an active
and constantly expanding presence in the Balkans, and a Greece
that fought for respect of international law and adherence to the
international treaties and contributed decisively to peace and
stability in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
