<HEADLINE> Germany Calls on EU to Double Aid for Aerospace Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany on Tuesday called on the
European Union (EU) to double its financial aid for aerospace
research to 700 million ecu (about 770 million U.S. dollars)
annually in order to improve its position in competition with the
U.S. aerospace industry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference in Bonn, German research and
technology minister Juergen Ruettgers also called for a better
coordination in aerospace research among EU members.
</P>
<P>
"Only by pooling efforts together can the European aerospace
industry survive the hard competition with the United States,"
Ruettgers said.
</P>
<P>
The German minister also stressed the need to complete the
process of restructuring the European Airbus Industrie consortium
into a share company as soon as possible. "Every delay will be a
competition advantage for the Boeing Corp.," he warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
