<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting Underway for Reconciliation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The first round of meeting of
the National Coordination Committee opened here on Tuesday to
prepare for the national reconciliation conference due to open at
the end of this month in Baidoa, southwest of Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, attended by the majority of the 28 member
committee- the signatories of the Cairo peace deal was co-charied
by Ali Mahdi Mohamed and Hussein Mohammed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
According to the short brief to the media by the two
co-chairmem, Ali Mahdi Mohamed said that a lot has been achieved
towards the reconcilation efforts. He said that they have just
begun to re-accelerate their talks in establishing an
all-inclusive administration for Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Hussein Mohamed Aidid said that their efforts have so far
proven successful after many obstacles have been overcomeed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the preparation for the Baidoa meeting is under
way, at which a national leadership council, a prime minister, a
parliament and a charter will be chosen for the future government
of Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The first results of the meeting will be disclosed on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
On March 28, the faction leaders are expected to announce
Mogadishu's administration which has collapsed the fall of the
late dictatorial regime in the country.
</P>
<P>
Technical committees are also working alongside the meeting of
the national Coordination Committee for the under ground
formalities and power sharing processes among various clans
living together in the Capital.  
</P>
