<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank Circular Bans Illegal Deposit encouragement Practices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
issued an urgent circular today, demanding that the practice of
attracting deposits through high interest rates should be firmly
stopped and seriously punished, so as to consolidate financial
order and protect the authority of the official interest rate.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the PBOC said the circular is targeted at some
commercial banks, urban and rural credit cooperatives, trust
investment companies and postal deposit departments which recently
used high interest rate to attract deposits. Their practices run
counter to the state's official interest rate policy.
</P>
<P>
A PBOC spokesman stressed that the interest rate published by
the PBOC is the state's official interest rate and should be
strictly obeyed. Practices run counter to the official interest
rate should be punished in accordance with the state's laws,
regulations and the PBOC's financial rules.
</P>
<P>
The circular demanded all related financial institutions carry
out self check-ups, examine and correct their self-styled
provisions which encouraged illegal deposit practices.
</P>
<P>
The circular also detailed the measures to punish illegal
practices which encourage deposits.
</P>
<P>
The central bank today also announced new interest rate
reduction effecting on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Died in Car Crashes in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Seven people died and 12
were injured in two road accidents in eastern South Africa
Tuesday, South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Six people died and eight, including a six-month baby, were
injured in a head-on collision between a light delivery vehicle
and a lorry in Pietermaritzburg in the coastal province of
KwaZulu-Natal, provincial traffic authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The lorry was allegedly travelling on the wrong side of the
road towards Pietermaritzburg when it collided with the other
vehicle shortly after noon, the authorities were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Six passengers on the back of the light delivery vehicle died
instantly and the lorry driver and four occupants apparently fled
the scene, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In a separate accident in the same province, a passenger died
and four others were injured Tuesday morning when the lorry they
were travelling in left the road and overturned, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The traffic authorities said it was believed that the lorry
driver lost control of the vehicle while negotiating a bend.
</P>
</TEXT>
