<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 250,000 people in Ethiopia Suffer From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's national
tuberculosis and leprosy control program announced Tuesday that
close to 250,000 people in the country are infected with the
virus that causes tuberculosis.
</P>
<P>
At a panel discussion held here to observe this year's World
Tuberculosis Day which falls on March 24, head of the program
Aleminesh Wolde said that up to 100,000 cases are registered
yearly in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
She said that tuberculosis which has been identified in
Ethiopia 40 years ago, has now become the leading killer disease
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The low awareness of the public about the contagious nature of
tuberculosis and the spread of HIV/AIDS aggravated the incidnece
of tuberculosis across the nation, she said, adding that
tuberculosis patients often tend to disrupt the treatment against
the disease, leading to the fast spread of tuberculosis
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occassion, representative of the World Health
Organization's tuberculosis and leprosy control program, Peter
Finstra said that tuberculosis victimizes one-third of the
world's population and that every 10 seconds one person loses his
life to tuberculosis in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-24 17:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian PM Demands Israeli Withdrawal From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Prime Minister Mahmoud
Zouebi Tuesday demanded Israel to pull out immediately from all
occupied Arab territories.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at the opening ceremony of the Near East
ministerial session of the U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization
(FAO), which opened here Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Zouebi said the U.N. Security Council resolutions 242 and 338
stipulates the full withdrawal of Israel from the occupied Arab
territories and its return to the June 4, 1967 borders.
</P>
<P>
The resolution 425 definitely calls for immediate and
unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zouebi reiterated Syria's stance on the issue, saying that
Syria has proclaimed its adherence to a just and comprehensive
peace in the region in line with international resolutions, the
Madrid decisions, and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian prime minister also called upon the U.S. and Russia,
the co-sponsors of the Middle East peace process, to deal with
Israel's rejection of any serious approach to a just and
comprehensive peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
At the FAO meeting, which was attended by agriculture ministers
from the Near East countries, Zouebi called for promoting
economic, cultural and technical cooperation among the FAO member
states.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of both the proposed Arab common
market and the Arab free trade zone in view of the fact that they
are the proper way for Arab economic intergration.
</P>
<P>
During the session, the agriculture ministers of the Near East
FAO member states would discuss a report by the FAO director
general Jacques Diouf, on the organization's activities in the
Near East and the FAO emergency plan for protection from animal
diseases and plant pests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
