<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Calls for Speedy Solution of Kosovo Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday called for a
speedy solution of the Kosovo problem through dialogue between
parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after meeting with visiting
Yugoslav Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic, Greek Parliament
President Apostolos Kaklamanis said that steps should be made as
soon as possible to seek a political solution of the Kosovo issue
and for a message of commencement of dialogue to be sent outwards.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Kosovo issue was an internal affair of
Yugoslavia, saying that Greece opposed the creation of "a separate
state entity" in Kosovo because such an eventuality would not
concern only Yugoslavia, but also all countries in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bulatovic, who arrived here Sunday for a three-day
official visit, said that Belgrade was willing to provide all the
minorities including the ethnic Albanians with all guarantees for
civil rights and freedoms, within the framework of Yugoslav
constitution and international treaties.
</P>
<P>
He condemned "foreign powers" for encouraging the ethnic
Albanians to seek Kosovo's independence from Yugoslavia, saying
that the development of Kosovo's situation depended on whether the
ethnic Albanians would come to the negotiating table with
Belgrade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
