<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Rolls-Royce Goes on Sale Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) - British car manufacturer
Rolls-Royce has produced the first new Rolls-Royce called "Silver
Seraph" for nearly 20 year, the company announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Silver Seraph, an entirely new motor car built with the
latest proven technology, uses the finest quality materials,
timeless craftsmanship and classic styling.
</P>
<P>
Exterior styling is an update of classic Rolls-Royce themes.
Its new V-12 engine, 5-speed automotive adaptive transmission and
new suspension have been developed for a swift, refined and
controlled driving experience.
</P>
<P>
The Seraph's new platform provides significantly increased body
torsional rigidity. New braking and traction assistance systems
also contribute to increased levels of driver control.
</P>
<P>
The new interior styling has equal impact, with careful detail
design complementating flowing shape and form. It features new
seats and trim, a new climate control system, new instruments and
controls.
</P>
<P>
Complex curvature has been applied to the fascia, console and
waistrails which unbleached burr veneers continue to be
individually mirror-matched throughout each motor car.
</P>
<P>
Graham Morris, Rolls-Royce Chief Executive, said that the
Silver Seraph would go on sale soon and it was "the dawn of a new
era for Rolls-Royce Motor Cars". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0042 </DOCNO>
