<HEADLINE> European Parliamentary Delegation Visits Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of British
members of the European Parliament headed by Glenys Kinnock,
arrived here Tuesday for a five-day working visit to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to journalists upon arrival, Kinnock said that the
mission aims to get first hand information about the social and
political conditions in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
She said the delegation will visit hospitals, clinics and
various projects being jointly undertaken by the European
Community and the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
During its stay here, the delegation will hold talks and
exchange views with members of the House of People's
Representatives of Ethiopia, she said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will also discuss with concerned bodies about
efforts underway by the Ethiopian government to expand education
and health services and improve the living standard of the
people, she added. 
</P>
