<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0057 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Militiamen in Somalia Attack UN Relief Convoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 24 (Xinhua)-- At least three people were
killed and more than five wounded on Tuesday when heavily armed
militiamen attacked a convoy of food aid in Mogadishu, capital of
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses Said that both the deceased and wounded are innocent
civilians caught in the cross fire. The deceased includes a
shopkeeper who tried to flee the fighting.
</P>
<P>
The shooting began when a convoy of more than 40 trucks of
food aid were attacked by unidentified gunmen on ex-21 October
road, said the eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
They said that cross-shooting between the armed escort of the
food aid and the attackers has resulted in the looting of three
lorries from convoy, while the rest are still being protected by
the escort.
</P>
<P>
The food, nearly 570 tons of porridge, lentils and cooking
oil, was on its way to the flooded regions of Southern Somalia
especially to the town of Buale and parts of the Lower Shabelle
region.
</P>
<P>
Food convoy from the World food Program of the United Nations
was halted Tuesday for security reasons, but will proceed to its
destination on Wednesday,said one of the food aid delivering
contractors who remained anonymous.
</P>
<P>
The lawlessness, killing, looting and burglary continue in the
Somali capital and its surrounding areas despite some political
developments among the faction leaders in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the militiamen in the area attributed the
attack to an earlier dispute between the two groups over a
contract for the transportation of the food aid to the flood
stricken regions of southern Somalia. Contract disputes often
lead to armed confrontations between the rival contractors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
