<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-24 18:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mordechai Briefs Annan on Israeli Initiative on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai on Tuesday briefed U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on his initiative about Israeli unilateral withdrawal from
South Lebanon based on U.N. resolution 425.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing after his meeting with Annan,
Mordechai said that it was a "good meeting" and he believed Annan
has gained a "whole idea" on Israel's initiative on a unilateral
Lebanese withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai reiterated that Israel urges the Lebanese government
to take responsibility in South Lebanon in the event of Israeli
pullout and fight against militant organizations like the
anti-Israeli Hezbollah (Party of God) guerrilla forces.
</P>
<P>
He also demanded the Lebanese government and forces protect
the safety of the pro-Israeli forces South Lebanese Army (SLA) if
Israel withdraws from the area. Israel is worried that the SLA,
which is accused by the Lebanese government of collaborating with
Israel, could turn their guns around against Israel if they are
abandoned by Israel.
</P>
<P>
"If that happens, Israel is ready to withdraw from South
Lebanon. We are in the area of South Lebanon only for one
reason: for the security of northern Israel," he said. Israel has
been fighting a tough guerrilla war against Hezbollah forces in
South Lebanon since 1985, paying a heavy price of annual high
death toll of Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Following the meeting with Mordechai, Annan headed directly for
a meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai did not disclose what response he got from the
U.N. chief during their one-hour meeting, but he called for help
from all friendly countries led by the United States to solve
the issue of South Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He warned that it is better to solve the problem before the
situation in South Lebanon worsens and before it is too late. He
was referring to the possible escalation of the fighting between
Israeli troops and the Hezbollah fighters, which will lead to
heavy casualties.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai will leave for Washington Wednesday for talks with
U.S. officials in an attempt to win the U.S. support for his
Lebanese withdrawal plan.
</P>
<P>
Annan is visiting Israel on the last leg of his first Middle
East tour since he took office in January 1997, which has
taken him to Jordan, Egypt, Lebanon, Syria and Palestinian
self-rule areas. He has repeatedly stressed that he came to
the region not as a mediator but to learn about the situation in
the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Israel pinned high hope on Annan to play a crucial role in
helping solve the Lebanese problem based on the U.N. resolution
425 that calls for Israeli unconditional withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Annan is to stay in Israel for another day Wednesday to hold
more talks with Israeli leaders before concluding his current
Middle East tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
