<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-24 18:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanon to launch Campaign to Fight Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon is going to launch a
13.1-million-dollar plan to fight increasing forest fires across
the country before summer, a statement from the Agriculture
Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the ministry will join hands with the
Interior Ministry to lead this campaign and submit the plan to the
council of ministers for approval.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, which is to be partially funded by the French
government, 15 fire-watch stations will be set up and 150 water
storage tanks, three helicopters, a number of fire engines and
communications equipment will be available.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that through the campaign it wants to reduce
the forest fires and increase the percentage of land covered by
forest from an estimated 6 percent to 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry's statistics, the number of fires
fell from 112 in 1995 to 79 in 1996, but jumped significantly to
127 last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of these forest fires were caused by carelessness, the
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
