<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Privatize National Bank of Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania plans to
privatize the National Bank of Commerce (NBC) by October, the
bank's public relation manager Ngalimecha Ngahiyoma said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Parastatal Sector Reform Commission (PSRC) has already
started handling procedures and looking into the best way to
privatize the bank, Ngahiyoma told reporters in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
He said the P.A. Consultants of the United Kingdom who are
engaged in operational matters, Dar es Salaam-based Advocate
company that is responsible for legal matters, and Messers
Masteller of the United States that is in charge of public
relations, have almost completed their missions.
</P>
<P>
Messers Price Water House of the United Kingdom still retains
some officials at the NBC head office but their mission will end
up soon, he said.
</P>
<P>
Matters of privatization of the NBC are being handled by
Andrew Chenge, the attorney general, who said advisory ideas will
be forwarded to higher authorities.
</P>
<P>
According to 1996/97 review and the action plan for 1997/98 of
PSRC, the National Micro Financing Bank will also be privatized
by June this year, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
