<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New UNDP Assistance in Congo to Benefit Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program is providing 182,000 U.S. dollars in
preparatory assistance to help formulate a major program in the
Congo to improve the economic, social and legal status of women,
and to assist women victims of the recent civil war, a release
from UNDP said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A survey will be conducted on the legal status of women in the
Congo to ensure that national legislation is in accordance with
international conventions.
</P>
<P>
The program will also fund micro-credit schemes and a
national gender sensitivity program. A "Maison de la Femme" will
be created in Brazzaville where women in distress can seek support
and help. Counseling will also be offered to victims of sexual
violence.
</P>
<P>
"The program is a major endeavor that aims to help women
recover from the disastrous war and to empower them to contribute
to the country's long-term stability and development," said
Dominique Ait-Ouyahia McAdams, UNDP Resident Representative in the
Congo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0077 </DOCNO>
