<HEADLINE> South Africa, Iran Receive Disaster Preparedness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP)'s Crisis Committee has allocated
250,000 U.S. dollars to strengthen the National Disaster
Management Authority in South Africa and 150,000 to improve
disaster response and coordination in Iran, a release from UNDP
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The support to Iran will improve the Government's ability to
lessen the impact of disasters and to improve readiness and
response. The initiative will make possible technical exchanges in
disaster work with neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
In South Africa, the assistance will strengthen the national
authority for disaster management by providing equipment and
training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
