<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Enhance Port Coop with Holland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A joint venture will soon be set
up between Mozambique's Public Corporation of Ports and Railways
and Cornelder Holding B.V. of Holland for a container and
ordinary cargo dock in Beira Port in central Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed here Tuesday by Anneke van Dok-van Weele,
visiting Dutch Minister of Foreign Trade, before ending her
two-day visit and leaving for home, the Mozambique News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, negotiations for the establishment
of the joint venture to be named Cornelder Mozambique, have
entered the final stage.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Mozambique, van Dok had held talks with
Tomaz Salomao, Mozambican Minister of Planning and Finance, and
Oldemiro Baloi, Minister of Industry, Trade and Tourism, on port
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
She also disclosed that the two countries will cooperate in
administrating Mozmabique's three development corridors to
promote railway transport between Mozambique and other countries
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Several Dutch companies have been cooperating with Beira Port
in the past 11 years, especially in its administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
