<HEADLINE> Two Killed, 13 Wounded in Arkansas School Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and 13 others were wounded when two boys spreed at a
group of middle school students in Jonesboro, Arkansas, Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Two suspects, ages 11 and 13, were taking into custody after
the 12:40 p.m. shooting outside Westside Middle School.
</P>
<P>
Among the wounded were two teachers and others were little
girls. The two shooters were 11 and 13 respectively. They were
lying in nearby woods.
</P>
<P>
The boys were taken to the county jail. Two rifles and other
weapons were recovered.
</P>
<P>
The school has about 250 students in sixth and seventh grades.
It was unclear whether the suspects were students at the school.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
