<HEADLINE> EU Approves Accession Partnership Guidance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission approved
on Wednesday accession partnership programs for the 11 applicant
countries for European Union membership.
</P>
<P>
The program forms a key part of the enhanced pre-accession
strategy aimed at guiding the applicants toward EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Each accession partnership program will support the applicant
country in its preparation for membership by setting out both the
priority areas for further work identified from the commission's
opinions and the financial assistance from the EU available to
help tackle problems.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the accession partnership programs cover such
areas as strengthening democracy and the rule of law, protection
of minorities, economic reform, reinforcement of institutional and
administrative capacity, preparation for full participation in the
internal market, justice and home affairs, agriculture,
environment, transport, employment and social affairs, regional
policy and cohesion.
</P>
<P>
The accession process is scheduled to be formally launched on
March 30 by EU foreign ministers with Cyprus, Bulgaria, Estonia,
Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, the Czech Republic, Romania,
Slovenia, and Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Accession negotiations will start on March 31 with Cyprus, the
Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Poland and Slovenia, the chosen
countries for the first wave of EU enlargement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
