has decided to lower the interest rate by 0.4 percentage point to
12.2 percent due to the decline of inflation, the Jerusalem Post
reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the third cut over three months and bring the
interest rate down to the lowest level since July 1994.
</P>
<P>
RIYADH -- Under an agreement signed on Tuesday, Saudi Arabia
will grant Eritrea a loan of 20 million dollars to finance the
execution of a vegetation project and construction of a road.
