<HEADLINE> Dhaka Committed to Attracting Direct Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
strongly committed to attracting direct foreign investment in
different sectors, the national agency BSS reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Farooq Sobhan, executive chairman of the
Board of Investment (BOI) while briefing a visiting Singaporean
trade mission in Dhaka Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sectors open to direct foreign investment include
infrastructure development, power and gas, telecommunications,
transport, housing, textiles, cement and steel plants, agro-based
industries, and sea and air ports building, according to the BOI
chief.
</P>
<P>
The government had liberalized its policies which include tax
holidays, repatriation of profits and providing the one-step
service by the BOI to investors, he stated.
</P>
<P>
He said that infrastructure development would be opened to
private sectors, especially for foreign direct investment, and a
number of agreements had already been signed with foreign
companies in the power and gas sectors.
</P>
<P>
New private companies had been floated in the
telecommunications sector, and the government was opening up this
area further with more deregulation, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the BOI's activities, he said its main objective were to
promote investment at home and abroad and take care of all the
requirements of investors through one-step service in setting up
new industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
