<HEADLINE> Romanians Face Third Price Hike This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Romanians are to face a new
round of price increases starting April 1, the third this year
after hikes in the VAT and the fuel.
</P>
<P>
The government approved an emergency ordinance on Tuesday,
requiring a new price calculation to be applied on products and
services delivered by state-owned corporations and other
monopolies.
</P>
<P>
The ordinance provides for an increase by 8.9 percent from
April 1 on railway and city transport fares, water charges,
sewerage services, Romanian-made medicines, and charges on
services provided by the Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The prices for gas and electricity are also likely to
increase. 
