<HEADLINE> Buyers Increase at HK Jewellery Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 16,000 buyers visited
the new wing of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center for
this year's Hong Kong International Jewellery Show from March
18-21, which represented an increase of 32.2 percent, said Hong
Kong Trade Development Council, the organizer.
</P>
<P>
Among the total number of buyers, more than 33 percent came
from overseas.
</P>
<P>
North America, including the United States and Canada, reported
the biggest percentage increase of 31 percent made by a region.
</P>
<P>
Other markets which registered significant growth in buyer
attendance included the Australia/Pacific region (27.6 percent),
Thailand (20 percent), Italy (14.5 percent) and Britain (26.9
percent).
</P>
<P>
The annual event, showcasing more than 770 companies from 27
countries and regions, occupied 24,360 square meters of exhibition
area. 
