<HEADLINE> McRae throws down gauntlet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Scot Colin McRae confirmed himself
as the firm favourite to win the Rally of Portugal through
Wednesday's first four specials on the final day of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
McRae, behind Spain's Carlos Sainz on the day's first race, set
the scratch times on the next two specials and came second behind
Belgium's Freddy Loix on the fourth special.
</P>
<P>
In the overall standings, the Scot led Loix by 16 seconds and
Sainz by 30 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Rally still had the last four specials to go later today.
</P>
</TEXT>
