<HEADLINE> Albanian Export Jumps 56 Percent in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Albania's exports stood at 2.5
billion leke (16 million U.S. dollars) in February, a 56.25
percent rise over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Of the total exports, one billion leke (6.25 million dollars)
came from Albanian-made products, signaling a recovery in
production of some industries after the country's political
turmoil last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports in February also increased 1.6 billion leke (10 million
dollars) to 9.7 billion leke (61 million dollars) from January.
</P>
<P>
The country still suffers a total trade deficit of 13.7 billion
leke (86 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
