<HEADLINE> Harvard to Design Leadership Program for HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- John F. Kennedy School of
Government (KSG) of Harvard University will design and organize a
high-level leadership enhancement program for senior officials of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) government, it
was announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Commissioned by the SAR's Civil Service Bureau (CSB), the
Leadership Enhancement And Development (LEAD) Program will be
developed and produced by KSG in collaboration with CSB and the
Civil Service Training and Development Institute.
</P>
<P>
The program, which is tailor made for the SAR civil service,
will provide an opportunity for the SAR government officials to
explore such issues as management, leadership, policy development
and the role of top level government officials in a changing
environment, according to a SAR government announcement here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the KSG has designed for a
government a tailor-made executive program which is to be held
outside the United States.
</P>
<P>
The program, set to be held in Hong Kong May 24-29 this year,
will be attended by some 30 senior civil servants at the senior
directorate level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
