<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tuberculosis Spreading in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The worldwide spread of
tuberculosis has hit Vietnam where the number of patients has
jumped by almost four percent in the last three years.
</P>
<P>
The number of patients has shot up to more than 73,000 last
year from 70,000 in 1995, according to figures released on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of people infected each year was around
130,000, meaning that half have not been diagnosed and receive no
treatment, said Nguyen Viet Co, director of the Tuberculosis and
Lung Diseases Institute of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Co said the number of patients who could not be cured was also
rising due to their uninformed abuse and overuse of medicines such
as antibiotics.
</P>
<P>
He said the National Tuberculosis Control Program had been
successful in 1997 in protecting 98 percent of the population from
the disease.
</P>
<P>
But the spread of TB increases in some remote and mountainous
areas with an infection rate of 200 people per 100,000, compared
with the rate of 48 per 100,000 in Hanoi and 93 per 100,000 in Ho
Chi Minh City.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam had set targets to curb the spread of TB up to the year
2000, added Co. It aimed to cure 85 percent of patients, diagnose
at least 70 percent of those infected, reduce the mortality rate
and prevent the misuse of antibiotics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
