<HEADLINE> India's Tornado Toll Mounts to 200 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The toll of tornado which
ripped through India's two eastern States of West Bengal and
Orissa Tuesday, has mounted to 200, Press Trust of India (PTI)
said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the dead, 175 were from the Midnapore district of West
Bengal alone. Officials said that nearly 500 people were still
feared trapped under the debris while another 3,000 were treated
for injuries.
</P>
<P>
Ten people were crushed to death as a country boat was lifted
20 feet in the rising Subarnarekha river and dashed against the
bank. Fifty passengers of a Midnapore-Sonakania bus were
critically injured when it was blown away into a canal by the
fierce winds. Over 10,000 heads of cattle also perished in the
storm, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue and relief operations are in full swing in the two
tornado-hit districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
