<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Third of Hungarians Travel on Holiday Every Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 25 (Xinhua) -- One third of Hungarians take a
travelling vacation at least once a year, spending a total 571
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures show that out of the ten million population,
three to 3.5 million go on tour once a year either at home or
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Greece, Italy, Austria and Romania are their favorite foreign
destinations, while the Balaton Lake and other mountain areas are
the major attractions at home.
</P>
<P>
Hungary is a highly developed tourist country, with the
tourist income accounting for ten percent of the Gross Domestic
Product.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, efforts have been made to tap the potential of
the home market. Country tours, hunting tours and warm spring
tours have emerged as new holiday themes.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that Hungarian tourism will grow over the next
few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
