The refinery, located in Dung Quat of the central Guang Nghai
province, will have a capacity of 6.5 million tonnes.
</P>
<P>
The official contract is expected to be signed by the end of
March, the Review said.
</P>
<P>
In order to begin operating by 2001, the two partners would
accelerate the process of establishing the joint venture, said
Levykin Sergey, representative of Zarubezhneft in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the joint venture is due to take place in
June or July, he added. 
