<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Textile Reform Proceeding Steadily, Officials Say (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ye said Zhejiang has taken the opportunity to advance the
structure of local industry and growth patterns of the local
economy to a new level.
</P>
<P>
In textile cities such as Ningbo, Hangzhou and Shaoxing, many
state-owned enterprises have begun to reorganize capital through
mergers or takeovers. Less-competitive enterprises have gone into
bankruptcy. About 10 large-enterprise groups are being formed with
competitive enterprises and products at their core.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that relocation of laid-off workers is the crucial part
of restructuring the industry.
</P>
<P>
The central government adopted a policy of "firmly pursuing
restructuring of the industry" while "showing care and sympathy
with workers in carrying out the move."
</P>
<P>
It adopted practical measures to divert and relocate laid-off
workers, especially those 40 and older.
</P>
<P>
Xu said these workers have made great contributions to the
development of the country's textile industry and made great
sacrifices in the reform. The government won't forget them, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the restructuring is focused on coastal
areas and major cities where social security systems are
relatively advanced. He expressed the belief that laid-off workers
will not cause conflicts because new jobs will be continuously
created in these regions as the economy grows and the service
sector prospers.
</P>
<P>
Ye said that Zhejiang is carrying out a well-scheduled plan to
lay off workers during the restructuring of the textile industry.
</P>
<P>
A total of 30,000 workers in the textile industry will be laid
off in the province this year, she said. The provincial government
gives priority to re-employing textile workers in its program to
help laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up five "safety nets" for laid-off textile
workers: minimum wages; minimum payments for subsistence; avoiding
layoffs of both husband and wife; exemption of medicare fees, rent
and public transportation fares; and government officials forging
person-to-person links with laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
Different levels of local governments in the province have
signed a document of responsibility with the provincial
government, undertaking goals of relocating a fixed number of
laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
Most of the laid-off workers have found new jobs through
various channels with the government's help. Among the 30,000
laid-off textile workers, only 4,300 have to rely on relief, which
is called "early retirement." Local governments, enterprises and
social insurance systems will share the expense of supporting
these people.
</P>
<P>
Ye pointed out that laid-off workers must also change their
ideology and expectations in finding new jobs. For example,
Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang, has more than 10,000 laid-off
workers at present. At the same time, about the same number of
laborers coming from outside the city are working in various jobs
there.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
