<HEADLINE> Qinghai Province Using Its Natural Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Qinghai Province, in northwestern
China, is trying to make the most of its natural resources to help
its economy and is planning an annual oil capacity of 5 million
tons and 5 billion cu.m. of natural gas by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Last year, it had 1.6 million tons of oil and gas, and
estimates show a potential in the Qaidam Basin in its western
parts of 15 trillion yuan worth of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
China's largest asbestos mine and potash fertilizer producer
are in the basin. The mine process 40,000 tons of material
annually.
</P>
<P>
The province will also have four major chemical projects to
produce 120,000 tons of polyvinyl chloride, 100,000 tons of
caustic soda, 200,000 tons of synthetic ammonia, and 300,000 tons
of urea annually by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
It now has four pillar industries in oil and gas, electricity,
chemical salts, and nonferrous metals, which contributed
handsomely to its industrial output of 11 billion yuan last year.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
