<HEADLINE> Philippines Welcomes Developments of Cambodian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
on Wednesday welcomed the latest developments in the Cambodian
situation, saying he was optimistic over the holding of free and
credible elections in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Ramos said he welcomed the full amnesty granted
by Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk to Prince Norodom Ranariddh and
the decision of the prince to return to Cambodia on March 30 1998.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said he was optimistic that these "very encouraging"
developments "will pave the way for the holding of free and
credible elections in Cambodia and the much-hoped restoration of
political stability in that country."
</P>
<P>
As current chairman of the ASEAN (Association of Southeast
Asian Nations) Standing Committee and the ASEAN Troika on
Cambodia, the Philippines takes a keen and active interest in the
evolution of the situation in Cambodia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Japan's peace plan and its acceptance by both the Cambodian
government and Ranariddh were the first breakthrough which
hopefully will improve the political environment in Cambodia, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos urged all parties concerned to once more demonstrate the
political will to implement fully the four pillars of Japan's
plan, particularly the cease-fire.
</P>
<P>
