Jukka Valtasaari and Philippine Trade and Industry Undersecretary
Melito Salazar.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Fidel Ramos welcomed the signing of the
agreement, saying it will pave the way for the expansion of
bilateral trade and economic cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
During his courtesy call on the president, Valtasaari said the
agreement will be the starting point for more massive Finnish
investments in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Valtasaari also informed Ramos of the possibility of the
linking up of small- and medium-scale industries in Finland with
those in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
He said among the areas where Finnish firms can link up with
local companies are shipping, energy production and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Concurring with Valtasaari, Ramos said the Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation Center for Small and Medium Enterprises is
one facility that could match small and medium enterprises in
Finland and the Philippines for possible link-up. 
