<HEADLINE> Tourism Booming in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of overseas visitors
to north China's Shanxi Province last year grew 29.2 percent over
1996 to reach 125,000 as a result of further improvements in the
local tourism sector.
</P>
<P>
This helped the province earn 37.48 million U.S. dollars in
foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of overseas tourists are coming from the
Republic of Korea, Russia, Singapore and Thailand along with
visitors from Japan, France, the United States and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Last year the province earned 4.37 billion yuan from the 18
million domestic tourists, a 36.57 percent rise from 1996. The
earnings went up 72 percent over 1996, the biggest growth rate
during recent years.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's major energy bases, Shanxi is enriched
with tourism attractions such as Wutai Mountain and Hukou
Waterfall. A number of new scenic spots have been developed to
attract visitors.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has become one of the leading local economic sectors.
</P>
