<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower, but interest on key
blue chips supported the indices to close higher Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Composite Index rose 4.89 points to 736.78,
the Emas Index added 1.07 points to 186.25 and the Industrial
Index increased 7.41 points to 1,313.06. However, the second board
index fell 1.31 points to 183.31.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 352 to 249, while 160 counters were
unchanged and 155 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover shrunk to 158.608 million shares valued at
418.409 million ringgit (115.518 million U.S. dollars) from
234.467 million shares worth 626.645 million ringgit (173.01
million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover fell to 145.220 million shares valued
at 381.726 million ringgit (105.39 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 211.452 million shares worth 564.260 million ringgit
(155.786 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover dropped to 13.388 million shares
valued at 36.682 million ringgit (10.127 million U.S. dollars)
from Tuesday's 23.015 million shares worth 62.385 million ringgit
(17.223 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deal eased to 5.753 million shares valued at 34.000
million ringgit (9.387 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's 28.723
million shares worth 90.208 million ringgit (24.905 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
One counter -- jeweller Habib Corporation -- was listed on the
second board, which opened 18 sen higher from its offer price of
2.60 ringgit and ended the day three sen lower at 2.57 ringgit
with 786 lots transacted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Uniphoenix Corporation, which was suspended as its
80 percent subsidiary Halim Securities Sdn Bhd had been placed
under the KLSE's direct supervision, resumed trading Wednesday and
lost 22 sen to 2.28 ringgit.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 5.571
million shares traded on the main board, industrial product 11.840
million shares, construction 18.810 million shares, trade/service
33.360 million shares, infrastructure 998,000 shares, finance
37.339 million shares, hotels 394,000 shares, properties 10.414
million shares, plantation 3.311 million shares, mining 367,000
shares, trusts 194,000 shares, closed-end fund 93,000 shares and
loans 22.528 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
