<HEADLINE> Special Chartered Train Now Available in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The people of Shanghai can now
charter a railway carriage on the Shanghai-Hangzhou express for
weddings, gatherings of friends, or business as of April 1.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that train cars can be hired by ordinary
citizens. In the past, the special carriages were available to
senior officials only.
</P>
<P>
For the cost of 5,000 yuan (600 US dollars), a person can
charter a luxurious carriage equipped with a drawing room,
kitchen, bathroom, and sound equipment.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-Hangzhou train will make the hour-and-a-half trip
from Shanghai to Hangzhou, the capital of China's Zhejiang
Province, three times a day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
