<HEADLINE> HK Official Offers to Provide More Flats to Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Hong Kong Housing
Authority Rosanna Wong stated here Wednesday that her department
will make efforts to provide more flats to local citizens and
enhance home ownership.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar entitled "Hong Kong Property Market: What Lies
Ahead," Wong said: "The Housing Authority's mission is to provide
a steady and sufficient supply of affordable housing for the less
fortunate in our community."
</P>
<P>
In his first Policy Address last October, Chief Executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa
outlined the blueprint of the SAR government's housing development
strategy, designed to "increase the overall home ownership rate to
70 percent..."
</P>
<P>
Discussing the current situation and prospects of the local
property market, some participants, including officials of the
Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce, local influential
economists and bankers, said that new home projects launched at
low price and attractive terms would enable to resolve the
home-lack problem in the SAR.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government's low price strategy for new home projects
will push down the land price, they said, noting that the land
price recorded at low level in the SAR in the passing months due
to the recent economic turmoil in Asia and will remain at low
level in Hong Kong in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
