<HEADLINE> Murder of Casino Official Condemned in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The killing of a senior official
who supervised Macao's casinos was strongly condemned here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Francisco Amaral, 45, chief of the Casino Inspection Division
under the Macao Casino Inspection and Coordination Department, was
shot in the head at noon on Tuesday near the well-known Casino
Lisboa. He was confirmed dead upon arrival at hospital.
</P>
<P>
The assassination is the latest murder connected with interests
conflicts between Macao casinos. At least two other senior
officials of the department have been shot since 1996.
</P>
<P>
A number of members of the Legislative Assembly (LA) said the
murder served a challenge to the security departments and damage
to social stability. They urged the government to take resolute
and effective measures to curb the spread of crimes.
</P>
<P>
"The murder of another senior civil servant is a very serious
case," said Tong Chi Kin, a Macao LA member. "It is an evident
challenge to the law, and tolerable to no one."
</P>
<P>
Another LA member, Vitor Ng, urged the government to seek a
fundamental resolution of problems concerning casino interests. If
the problems are not resolved promptly, he said, there might come
another wave of crimes, which will be a severe blow to the local
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Macao Daily News said in a commentary on
Wednesday that the worsening security situation in Macao over the
past few years has scared tourists away and make local residents
worry about their safety.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said the security departments should make the
utmost efforts to stop the crimes from happening again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
