<HEADLINE> Macao Trade Volume with Canada Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Macao's trade with Canada reached
59.085 million Canadian dollars (about 41.36 million U.S. dollars)
in 1997, up 34.4 percent from 1996, the Macao Daily News reported
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Canadian statistics as saying Canada imported
55.451 million Canadian dollars (38.81 million U.S. dollars) worth
of Macao goods and exported 3.634 million Canadian dollars (2.54
million U.S. dollars) worth of goods to Macao last year.
</P>
<P>
Canadian exports to Macao included metal products, computer
parts, newsprint, wooden products, heavy road construction
vehicles and aircraft parts.
</P>
<P>
Macao exported to Canada mostly garments, desk lamps, electric
appliances, footwear and frozen shrimps. 
