<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Large High-Tech Group Enters Domestic Laser-Jet Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University's Founder
Group Corp. announced here today that its laser jets are now
available on the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The Founder WordJet can increase the efficiency of office work
with the help of Founder's Chinese character-processing technology
that was originally used in printing composition, said Wang Xuan,
a member of the Founder Group's board of directors.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference today, Wang said Founder has 22
years of experience in printing composition and now controls 90
percent of the world market for Chinese language printing
composition.
</P>
<P>
The WordJet has preinstalled 20 character fonts, and produces
quality printouts at high speed, said Wang, who is also president
of the Founder R&AMP;D Center, adding that the printer has great
potential in the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese laser-jet market is now dominated by foreign
manufacturers, but the best are equipped with merely four
character fonts.
</P>
<P>
Founder expects an annual production of 20,000 WordJets, and
plans to bring the new products into the top three in the Chinese
laser-jet market this year. WordJets are projected to be one of
the top two laser-jet printers in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts say the birth of WordJet marks a breakthrough
in Chinese-developed laser-printing technology, as well as a great
leap forward in Founder's hardware manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Founder's brand name now appears on its computers, monitors and
terminals.
</P>
<P>
The total sales of Founder in 1997 was 5.85 billion yuan, an
increase of almost 50 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Research-and-development investment last year accounted for
4-to-5 percent of the related production value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
