<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Hong Kong Tourism Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Qian Qichen said
today that preparations are under way for increasing the number of
tourists from the inland areas to Hong Kong in a bid to prop up
tourism in the special administrative region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
While meeting a tourism delegation from Hong Kong, Qian said he
hopes that the cooperation between tourism industries of the
inland areas and the SAR would be further enhanced.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier said the inland areas and Hong Kong tourism
is closely interrelated and the prosperity of tourism in Hong Kong
will contribute to the development of tourism in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong can provide many precious experiences in developing
tourism to the inland areas, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong delegation is being led by Lo Yuk Sui, director
of the Hong Kong Tourism Association. 
</P>
