<HEADLINE> Ranariddh's Advance Team Arrives in Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 25 (Xinhua) -- An advance team for Prince
Ranariddh's return arrived here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The six-people team includes Prince Sisowath Sereirath,
Education Minister Toul Lous and Tourism Minister Veng Sereyvath.
</P>
<P>
Toul Lous told reporters upon the group's arrival at Po Chen
Tong International Airport that the team came back to prepare
Prince Ranariddh's return on March 30 and to check security
conditions for the return.
</P>
<P>
It will be the former First Prime Minister's first return to
Phnom Penh after his nearly nine months of self-exile. The prince was
deposed by Second Prime Minister Hun Sen last July in the wake of a
military conflict.
</P>
<P>
Plans have been made for the prince to stay at a well-known
hotel in Phnom Penh when he returns, said an official of
Funcinpec, a political party of which the prince is leader.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, government officials said no plans were being made
for additional security for the prince's arrival because he is no
longer a co-head of government.
</P>
<P>
"But of course, the Royal government and the Ministry of the
Interior will take every possible measure to protect Ranariddh as
well as any other politician," said Interior Ministry spokesman
Khieu Sopheak.
</P>
<P>
The prince will participate in the July 26 general elections
after his return. 
</P>
</TEXT>
