<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Olympic Committee Clears Bobsledder of Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Australian bobsledder Martin
Harland will not be sanctioned for doping, Australian Olympic
Commitee (AOC) announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
AOC said that Harland did not threaten its anti-doping policy
at the time of his incident because he was not a potential
Olympian when he took drugs.
</P>
<P>
Harland tested positive to the steroid stanozolol last
September and admitted at a hearing to taking the banned drug as
medication for a back injury in February 1997.
</P>
<P>
AOC Secretary-General Craig McLatchey said the National Sports
Dispute Center Committee could not make a saction under the AOC's
new anti-doping policy which came into effect for all positive
tests after December 1, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
