<HEADLINE> South Korean Soccer Team To Go on Tour in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's national soccer team
will travel to Europe next month for a series of friendlies in
their preparation for the World Cup finals in France this summer.
</P>
<P>
The 20-day tour will start in France April 6, when the South
Koreans will play the first of two games with French professional
clubs, South Korean soccer officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The squad then will move to Slovakia for a match with its
national team April 15. It is to play Macedonia on April 18 and
Yugoslavia four days later.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is one of 32 teams that will compete in the 1998
World Cup in France June 10-July 12. It will meet Mexico, Belgium
and the Netherlands in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
