<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker as Gold Loses Shine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar's break
above 67 U.S. cents proved short-lived Wednesday in Sydney as it
slipped lower when gold lost some of its recent strong luster.
</P>
<P>
The currency closed the local trading session at 66.87 U.S.
cents, down from 67.03 late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Steve North, a senior dealer of Chase Manhattan, said the
Australian dollar spent most of the day in a "holding pattern"
with little to drive it either way.
</P>
<P>
North said the unit's topple from its early high of 67.12 U.S.
cents coincided with a corresponding move in the price of gold in
New York overnight and Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
