<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Becomes Self-sufficient in Non-staple Food Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province has
become self-sufficiency in non-staple food supplies primarily
because of its "shopping basket" program, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The program was worked out by the state in 1988 to develop
production of non-staple foods and ensure urban supply.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi, one of the country's most important centers for heavy
chemicals, has invested 10 million yuan annually since 1991 to
develop non-staple food bases in its six major cities, and
industrial and mining areas.
</P>
<P>
The province also built dozens of fresh vegetable and livestock
companies to provide urban residents with a constant supply.
</P>
<P>
While setting up large- and medium-size feed-processing plants
in major cities, the province has made efforts to establish farms
for raising pigs, chicken, fish and cattle.
</P>
<P>
The adoption of technological innovation has allowed a group of
modern non-staple processing centers to emerge, which basically
meet the demand of different consumers.
</P>
<P>
The efforts have paid off and as a result, local people's
living conditions have improved a great deal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
