<HEADLINE> China's First On-Line College Goes Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The first on-line college in
China went operational recently in Xi'an, the capital of Shaanxi
Province, Beijing's "Economic Reference Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new higher-education computer network, which is sponsored
by the Shaanxi Finance Institute and the Xi'an Xunye Golden
Network Information Telecommunication Co.Ltd will offer computer
accounting classes for anyone with access to the computer network.
</P>
<P>
The two years of schooling consist of 13 subjects and students
who pass the higher education exam will receive approved
certificates.
</P>
<P>
The on-line college is open to students round-the-clock, and
they can go to class whenever they want. 
