<HEADLINE> Sinking Urban Areas to be Rehabilitated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government will
allocate 200 million yuan (25 million U.S. dollars) for
rehabilitating and treating the sinking areas of Benxi, a
coal-producing city in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The sinking areas, caused by over-exploration, emerged during
the Japanese occupation of China's northeast regions. They are
1-to-2 meters below ground level, which causes problems for
residents during the rainy seasons.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year the governments had allocated 78.5
million yuan for rehabilitating an area of 2.2 sq. km. with 4.3
sq. km. of urban area remaining to be rehabilitated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
