<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector Becoming Important In Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The private sector has been
playing an increasingly bigger role in the economy of northwest
China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The landlocked and under-developed province, on the
Qinghai-Tibetan Plateau, has increased the number of private
enterprises from 46,350 to 74,800 in the past five
years. Registered capital of such enterprises grew from 186
million yuan to 2.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai's private sector employs 140,000 people and paid 94
million yuan in taxes in 1997, an increase of 33.9 percent from
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 percent of the revenues of two districts in Xining, the
provincial capital, comes from the private sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
