<HEADLINE> Tianjin Sees Increasing Number Of Internet Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of Internet users has
been growing rapidly in the northern Chinese port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
According to the Municipal Scientific and Technology
Commission, the number of Internet users was up to 10,000 last
year, and has kept growing by more than 1,000 a month since the
beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal Data Telecommunications Bureau spent 30 million
yuan last year in expanding its capacity for Internet users.
</P>
<P>
Most institutional Internet users are in foreign trade
enterprises, joint ventures, and some large state-owned
enterprises, and most individual Internet users are adults
involved in scientific research, education, or the computer
industry, or middle school and college students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
