<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New MOFTEC Minister on China's Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- New Chinese Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic cooperation Shi Guangsheng told Xinhua here
today that he shoulders great responsibility and confronts arduous
tasks.
</P>
<P>
Having worked for China's foreign trade sector for almost four
decades, Shi has a sober and unique understanding of the current
situation of China's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Great strides have been made in foreign trade since China
adopted its reform and opening-up policy 20 years ago. Last year,
China became the 10th largest foreign trade country. It has been
ranked No.2 for five consecutive years in terms of the value of
foreign investment introduced. Major headway has also been made in
economic cooperation with foreign countries, providing assistance
to other countries, and reforming the foreign trade and management
systems.
</P>
<P>
However, Shi said there are many challenges and difficulties as
well:
</P>
<P>
-- No access to the World Trade Organization brings many
unfavorable competitive factors to China in the international
market;
</P>
<P>
-- And worldwide trade protectionism has often adversely
affected the development of China's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese state-owned foreign trade businesses are not
capable of fully catering to the demands of the market economy and
China's export structure needs to be optimized, he said.
</P>
<P>
Facing the difficulties, Minister Shi -- a frank, open and
humorous man -- said that challenge means opportunity.
</P>
<P>
Since he formed an indissoluble bond with the foreign trade
business when he was admitted as a student at the Beijing Foreign
Trade Institute at the age of 21, he has overcome various
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
After he was assigned to the then Ministry of Foreign Trade, he
was sent to work in the Commercial Offices of the Chinese
Embassies to Mali and Belgium. Since 1974, he worked for the China
Metals and Minerals Import and Export Corp. for 12 years.
</P>
<P>
Later, he was dispatched by MOFTEC to Shanghai, China's
largest industrial city and trade center. Two years later, he went
back to Beijing and was promoted to the position of director of
MOFTEC's Import and Export Department.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, he became the assistant MOFTEC minister and, two
years later, vice foreign trade minister.
</P>
<P>
His rich knowledge and experience in foreign trade business,
strict work style, adherence to principles and pragmatic approach
have enabled him to surmount difficulties one after another.
</P>
<P>
Touching upon China's foreign trade situation at present, Shi
said there are still many development opportunities and, at the
same time, the influence of the financial crisis in Asia on
China's foreign trade, especially on export and introduction of
foreign trade, should not be underestimated.
</P>
<P>
"Even though, we must strive to expand exports and positively
absorb foreign investment," he added.
</P>
<P>
To increase exports, the foreign trade companies must reduce
production costs to sharpen their competitive edge and streamline
the export structure, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the the new preferential policies for
absorbing foreign investment should be implemented as soon as
possible. Government should improve its services to ensure the
healthy development of the foreign-funded businesses in China, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
