<HEADLINE> Clinton Starts Three-Hour Visit to Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
arrived in Kigali, capital of Rwanda, Wednesday for his scheduled
brief visit to the central African country.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that my trip... will help to avoid further killing
along ethnic lines and bring the attention of the world to this
in a way that will have an impact on ethnic conflicts in other
parts of the world," Clinton told reporters before departing from
Entebbe, Uganda for his three-hour stop in Kigali.
</P>
<P>
Clinton planned to meet survivors of Rwanda's 1994 genocide
and pledged U.S. help to prevent a recurrence of such massacres
during his whirlwind visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda is the third leg of Clinton's six-nation Africa tour,
and the only country among the six nations, which is still
haunted by unstability and bloodshed.  
</P>
