<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Development Zone Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The hi-tech development zone in
Guangdong province's Shantou will become an industrialization
experiment zone in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The zone in the northeastern part of the city was established
in 1993 and has 1.8 billion yuan in investment now in its 4 sq.km.
</P>
<P>
It has 122 enterprises with a total investment of 6.3 billion
yuan. The enterprises mainly cover electronic information, biology
projects, and energy saving technology.
</P>
<P>
To increase development, the city government has unified
management in order to simplify procedures and provide better
service for investors. It plans to get on the Internet to develop
local industry.
</P>
<P>
Shantou is one of China's five Special Economic Zones and is
the home of three million overseas Chinese, many of whom are
entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Its technological advantages have helped develop hi-tech
industries like ultrasound equipment, machinery, and plastics.
</P>
</TEXT>
