<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
will hold a tourism festival from April 18 to May 23 at the
Meiling tourism zone in Nanchang, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, acrobat Feng Jiushan plans to set a
new world high-wire record on a 760-meter cable across a river.
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old Feng set the world record on a 730-meter cable
across Hukou Falls on the Yellow River in less than 36 minutes on
August 25, 1996, breaking the previous record set by the
Canadian-American "prince of the air" Jay Cochrane, who crossed a
640-meter cable across the Three Gorges of the Yangtze River in 58
minutes in 1995.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, people can enjoy a series of cultural
activities like a religious fair, butterfly exhibition, circus
acts, acrobatic performances, and folk arts, and the local
government will open a number of historical relics and natural
spots to tourists. 
</P>
