<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Hepatitis Virus Confirmed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Scientists have confirmed the
first case in China of TTV, the seventh kind of virus which can
cause hepatitis, according to today's Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
Wang Haitao, a professor with the Military Academy of Medical
Sciences, together with two of his colleagues, discovered the
first case in China involving a TTV infection. They also cloned a
gene segment of the new virus from the sufferer's serum.
</P>
<P>
Japan first found the virus in December of 1997 with the use of
cloning technology and named it TTV. The virus can be spread
through blood transfusions.
</P>
<P>
China has a high incidence of hepatitis. Scientists believed
the discovery will play a positive role in the study of
hepatitis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
