<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents Have Highest Scientific Awareness in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey has shown that
the people of Beijing have the highest level of scientific
awareness in China, and the people there respect teachers,
scientists, and technologists most.
</P>
<P>
The study was done by the Beijing Science and Technology
Commission, Beijing Association of Science and Technology, and
Beijing Research Institute of Science and Technology Information
among 3,500 people between the ages of 18 and 69.
</P>
<P>
It involved knowledge of science, understanding of scientific
research, and impact of science and technology on society. The
study showed that the public scientific level reached four percent
in Beijing, much higher than the national average of 0.3
percent. According to a similar survey in the United States, their
public scientific level reached 6.9 percent at the end of 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The study showed that 65.7 percent of the people in Beijing
believe that science and technology's advantages outweigh the
disadvantages and more than 80 percent think that science and
technology serves as an important motive force in developing
industry and agriculture, promoting economic growth and improving
living standard, and 45.7 percent believe that science and
technology can solve most of the problems we are confronted with.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicated that the public are concerned about
research on cancer and other difficult diseases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
