<HEADLINE> Beijing Encourages Urban Jobless to Earn Bread In Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Jobless Beijing urban residents
are encouraged to earn their bread in the countryside by opening
up waste hilly land.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with a new policy of the Beijing Municipal
People's Government, jobless urban dwellers can contract waste
hilly land for 50 years with tax exemption of one to three
years on their products.
</P>
<P>
The new farmers can enjoy reduced tax or tax-free policies when
their harvests are hit by natural disasters or other unavoidable
calamities.
</P>
<P>
Urban dwellers who find "new employment" in the rural areas can
still enjoy unemployment subsidies, according to the new policy.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has 35,000 registered jobless people. About 170,000
people have been laid off. Laid-off people are not counted in the
number of jobless people because they still receive some bottom
line benefits from their employers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
