<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Secondary Education in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved
Tuesday a credit of 48 million U.S. dollars to help finance a
secondary education project in the African country of Malawi.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said the project is designed to create more
educational opportunities for school-age children, especially
girls and students in rural areas. The project will also help
upgrade teaching and studying facilities of secondary schools,
with a special AIDS-prevention education course, the official said.
