<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, Indonesia Investigate Illegal Immigration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka and Indonesia are
jointly investigating an international racket in the trafficking
of illegal immigrants, The Daily News quoted Foreign Ministry
sources as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Five such immigrants who were arrested last week at Jakarta
International Airport while on their way to Australia are under
interrogation, the sources told the paper Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Another group of ten who were arrested in similar circumstances
also at the Jakarta International Airport were deported back to
Sri Lanka and are now in police custody.
</P>
<P>
They were carrying forged boarding passes and air tickets of an
international airline when they were arrested.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that several agencies in Colombo are producing
these forged travel documents and supplying them to an Indonesian
contact.
</P>
<P>
Assistance of the Australian government is also to be sought in
tracking down the racketeers, the paper added. 
