<HEADLINE> Romania to Endorse Program for Accession to EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Romanian government will
endorse a program on Thursday for Romania's accession to the
European Union (EU), the Romanian News Agency Rompres reported.
</P>
<P>
The enabling bill, the National Program for Accession, will be
submitted to the EU on March 30. It includes the country's
targets, priorities in short and medium terms, concrete measures
to fulfil them, financial implications and specific deadlines.
</P>
<P>
The program is composed of three parts: Romania's Economic
Program for Short and Medium Terms, the Public Administration
Reform Program and the National Plan for the Community.
</P>
<P>
Romania will send a delegation to a Brussels' meeting scheduled
on March 30. There, the EU's trading partners, Poland, the Czech
Republic, Hungary and Slovenia, along with Estonia and Cyprus, are
scheduled to open membership negotiations with the EU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
