<HEADLINE> Serbia's New Government Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The National Assembly of the
Republic of Serbia of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Tuesday
approved a new cabinet headed by Prime Minister Mirko Marjanovic.
</P>
<P>
A declaration of national unity was also approved at the close
of the assembly session.
</P>
<P>
The new national unity government consists of 16 members of the
Socialist Party of Serbia (SPS), 15 members of the Serbian Radical
Party (SRS), four members of the United Left (JUL) and one
nonparty member.
</P>
<P>
The five deputy prime ministers are: Milovan Bojic (JUL), Ratko
Markoric (SPS), Tomislar Nikolic (SRS), Dragomir Tomic (SPS) and
Vojislar Seselj (SRS).
</P>
<P>
Marjanovic, on his second term at the post, said the new
government would give priority to economic development and the
Kosovo issues.
</P>
<P>
National Assembly Chairman Dragan Tomic hailed the inauguration
of the government and the issue of the declaration of national
unity. He said there could be no hope and future for the country
without national unity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
