<HEADLINE> EU to Provide Aid for Infrastructure Projects in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
provide Albania with 190 million ECUs (175 million U.S. dollars)
this year to help the country implement its infrastructure
projects, an official of the European Commission said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the end of a two-day meeting of the Albania-European Joint
Commission, officials from the 15-nation EU and Albania held talks
on the ways to further promote political and economic cooperation
between Albania and the EU.
</P>
<P>
The talks also covered Albania's economic development, security
situation, administrative reforms and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The EU said it supports Albania in its bid to join the World
Trade Organization (WTO). The EC, which is the executive body of
the EU, decided to send an expert team to Albania, commissioned to
enhance bilateral trade and cooperation, it was announced at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after the meeting, the EU called for
Albania to make greater efforts to stablize its national situation
so as to attract more foreign investment. In this regard, it
asked Albania to get rid of companies engaged in fraudulent
investment schemes.
</P>
<P>
Albania held its first talks with the EU in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
