<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Cuts Down Public Spending </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Spain has saved some 56.98 billion
pesetas (about 370 million U.S. dollars) through a package of
austerity measures adopted last year.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Economy and Finance told a
parliamentary panel that these measures included best utilization
of public assets and a cut on administrative expenditure and
public spending.
</P>
<P>
He said that through the rent or sale of vacant public
buildings alone, the government got 36.37 billion pesetas (236
million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Spain has down-sized the government, reduced business trips and
postal fee, and cut down on government publications. About 15.08
billion pesetas (98 million dollars) have been thus saved.
</P>
<P>
Another 4.93 billion pesetas (32 million dollars) are saved as
office-use goods are bought by wholesale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
