<HEADLINE> Philippine Police Kill 5 Carnappers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Philippine policemen shot dead
five suspected carnappers in a gun battle in a province northwest
of Manila, police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the suspects, armed with firearms, were aboard a
stolen Toyota car Tuesday night when cornered by the traffic
policemen along a highway in Nueva Ecija province.
</P>
<P>
The policemen shot at the suspects who first fired at the
pursuing law enforcers. Recovered from them were three short
firearms, ammunition and the bullet-riddled car.
</P>
<P>
Police said the suspects stole the said car in Makati city,
Metro Manila on November 2 last year. 
</P>
