<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3000 Wait for Heart Operations in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's National Hospital in
Colombo has a waiting list of 3,000 patients for heart operations
and most of them are children with congenital heart defects, The
Daily News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted hospital sources as saying that due to the
limited facilities available at the hospital only about 400
operations could be done annually.
</P>
<P>
Until the heavy backlog is reduced, the hospital will not list
new patients for operations.
</P>
<P>
A Sri Lankan doctor, Dudley Halpe, residing in the United
States, has recently come to Sri Lanka with a team of heart
surgeons from the United States and conducted 12 complicated
pediatric operations which could not be done by local doctors, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Annually in Sri Lanka about 2,500 children are born with
congenital heart conditions. Some of them die a few months after
birth and some recover naturally while about 2,000 have to undergo
surgery.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has three hospitals which conduct major heart
surgery. A considerable number of major heart operations including
by-pass ones are conducted at these hospitals, enabling patients
to get treatment for their conditions without going abroad, the
paper added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
