<HEADLINE> Jaermann Wins Second Stage in Spain Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Rolf Jaermann of Switzerland won
the second stage of the Catalan Week cycling race on Tuesday in
Castello d'empuries, Spain.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss bursted out some 12 kilometers from the sprint line
and finished several seconds before other riders.
</P>
<P>
Jaermann overcame teammate Stephane Barthe to be the overall
leader with a 20-second gap.
</P>
<P>
Italians Filippo Casagrande and Paolo Bettini finished second
and third repectively.
</P>
<P>
Hard wins hauled riders to finish over one hour more than
expected in the 161-kilometer stage.
</P>
<P>
The race was also hindered when a car slipped through police
controls and was driving towards riders, while most of the leading
group and several team cars took the wrong turning with about 20
kilometers left to ride.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's stage will be the toughest as the 174-kilometer
course is to run over the Rasos de Peguera hill from Castello
d'Empuries to Berga. 
</P>
</TEXT>
