<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, Russian Cooperation to Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said Tuesday that despite the reshuffle of the Russian
cabinet, his country will continue to cooperate with Russia,
especially regarding integration between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"What happened in Russia is a normal affair of constitution. It
is a natural process to reshuffle the government, particularly
during a complicated transitional period," Nazarbayev said Tuesday
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
To accelerate reforms in Russia needs new strength and new
thoughts, he said. It has occurred before in Kazakhstan and other
countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Kazakhstan and Russia will continue to
develop despite the change in Russia, he said. Russian President
Boris Yeltsin has declared that Russia's current economic policy
will not change, and it will benefit peoples of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin appointed Energy Minister Sergei Kiriyenko as acting
prime minister after he sacked Viktor Chernomyrdin and the entire
cabinet on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle came after Yeltsin censured the government during
weekend meetings for its chronic failure to pay back wages and
pensions to millions of Russians. 
</P>
