<HEADLINE> Tibetans Using Post Offices To Save Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The residents of Lhasa, the capital
of the Tibet Autonomous Region, never thought they could get cash
elsewhere in China with just a savings card provided by the city's
post office.
</P>
<P>
This is the case, however, now that the post office in Lhasa
has joined a postal savings network in 44 cities like Beijing,
Shanghai, Chengdu, and other provincial capitals.
</P>
<P>
This means Tibetans don't have to carry much cash with them
when they travel to any of the 44 cities.
</P>
<P>
Lhasa's post office is also expected to ATM service at the end
of 1998, by which time getting cash will be even simplier, said
the official. 
</P>
