prosecutors' office has been set up in Colombia to fight money
laundering by South American drug cartels, reports said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The office comprises 33 prosecutors, 30 judicial technicians
and 39 judicial assistants, one engineer and a systems analyst. It
will receive support from the technical investigation corps of
Colombia's public prosecutor's office.
</P>
<P>
The new office will deal with companies that administer illicit
properties acquired mainly by the "cali," "medellin" and "norte
del valle" drug cartels.
</P>
<P>
The office is led by Alfonso Gomez Mendez, attorney general of
the country. 
