<HEADLINE> Germany to Help Bulgaria Join EU, Revive Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany will help Bulgaria in its
future talks with the European Commission on the country's
accession to the European Union (EU), German Minister of Economics
Guenter Rexrodt told Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov at a
meeting here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rexrodt, who arrived here Monday with a large business
delegation, told reporters after the meeting that he was confident
the accession talks would start shortly.
</P>
<P>
Referring to German assistance to the recovery of Bulgaria's
economy, Rexrodt said that a state bank for small and medium-sized
business promotion will be established in Bulgaria with German
capital within a few weeks.
</P>
<P>
He said the pending establishment of a bank promoting small and
medium-sized business and banking privatization in Bulgaria would
help the recovery of the Bulgarian economy.
</P>
<P>
Kostov said during the meeting that although Germany is the
number one investor in Bulgaria, the size of German investment is
extremely insufficient.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, agreements were signed between Siemens and
the Energy Committee, and between the Bulgarian Chamber of
Commerce and Industry and Berlin's Chamber of Wholesale and
Foreign Trade.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference with Bulgarian Trade and Tourism
Minister Valentin Vassilev, Rexrodt expressed satisfaction with
the development of Bulgarian-German trade and economic relations,
and stressed they had a vast, still untapped potential.
</P>
<P>
Rexrodt's visit is the first by a German minister of economics
in 13 years. The large business delegation is indicative of the
strong interest German businessmen are showing in Bulgaria, said
Rexrodt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
