Italian Foreign Minister said.
</P>
<P>
After talks with Dini, Albright left Rome for Bonn, where a
Contact Group meeting was scheduled on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The six-nation Contact Group on former Yugoslavia, which
includes Britain, France, Italy, Germany, the U.S. and Russia, was
established to bring peace to the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Albright will chair Wednesday's meeting. It will consider
whether or not to impose new sanctions on Yugoslavia because of
the recent ethnic conflicts in the Serbian province of Kosovo.
