press conference that the two-day meeting had accomplished all its
goals. These were an assessment in each of the candidates'
countries for integration with the EU, and a strengthening of
inter-parliamentary dialogue.
</P>
<P>
"To the European Parliament, such meetings are a transfer of
activity to the parliaments of the central and east-European
countries," Jose Maria Gil-Robles said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that EU associated countries had to have the same
relations with the European Parliament as the member states did.
