<HEADLINE> High Winds, Snowstorms Blast Much of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Gusty winds, snow, torrential rain
and lower temperatures that hit much of Italy Tuesday have created
havoc in the country.
</P>
<P>
The accumulation of snow in the northern mountainous areas
reached 1.3 meters, and central Italy received a downpour of
torrential rain. Snow also covered the southern slopes of
Vesuvius, a volcano in the region of Naples.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, temperatures in most parts of Italy dropped sharply,
with the average temperature dipping 3-5 degrees lower than the
same period over the past years.
</P>
<P>
The severe winter weather has created havoc in the
country. Road traffic has been disrupted, schools closed in some
villages and fishermen were trapped in port by strong winds. Fruit
output this year is also expected to decrease by about 40
percent. 
</P>
