<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
plans to reap more grain and cotton output in 1998 after two
years' successive good harvest.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province plans to produce 34 million tons of grain
and 400,000 tons of cotton this year, said an official of the
provincial planning commission.
</P>
<P>
