<HEADLINE> McRae Maintains Lead, Loix Chases Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Britain held onto
his lead but had his leading advantage cut down to 11.3 seconds
over closely chasing Belgian Freddy Loix in the Rally of Portugal
on Tuesday in Oporto, Portugal.
</P>
<P>
McRae, in a Subaru, crashed out for a puncture on stage 14 in
the second leg of the race and lost almost 40 seconds to the
chasing pack.
</P>
<P>
Loix, who started slowly in his Toyota with the 10th-quickest
time on the opening stage, won four stages at the end of the day,
putting up more pressure on MeRae prior to the final day on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Current world championship leader Spaniard Carlos Sainz drove a
Toyota to third with 16 seconds behind Loix, after lost 20 seconds
on a broken rear brake pipe on stage 13.
</P>
<P>
On stage 12, world champion Tommi Makenen of Finland crashed
out the race after his Mitsubishi hit a tree.
</P>
<P>
The three-day race will end in Matosinhos, Oporto, after
Wednesday's 100.58 kilometers eight-stage race. 
</P>
