<DOCNO> XIE19980325.0337 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Locals Save Snow Leopard In Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A snow leopard saved by some local
people sent to a zoo in Urumqi, capital of northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, on Monday for treatment.
</P>
<P>
On March 20, the 2-year-old leopard fell into a hole on an
ice-covered reservoir while hunting for food. The animal tried to
climb up for five hours, but couldn't get out.
</P>
<P>
When some construction workers saw the animal, they immediately
reported it to their leaders, and began organizing the rescue work.
</P>
<P>
After struggling in the freezing water for over 10 minutes,
they managed to get the leopard onto the bank.
</P>
<P>
The animal, which is a meter in length and weighs 60 kg, is
suffering from a cold and some internal injuries, but
veterinarians at the zoo are giving it special attention.
</P>
<P>
The snow leopard is on the verge of extinction and lives mainly
in snowy Himalayan and Altay mountains. It is under state
protection of the Chinese government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
