<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finnish FM says Ties with Russia not affected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Foreign Minister Tarja
Halonen said Tuesday that the change of government in Russia will
not affect its ties with Finland because the two countries enjoy
good relations.
</P>
<P>
Halonen made the remark at a joint press conference with her
visiting Albanian counterpart, Paskal Milo.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Monday suddenly dissolved
the government headed by Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin
because of its failure to solve the country's socio-economic
problems.
</P>
<P>
Russia can play a strong and constructive role in international
cooperation, Halonen said. She expressed hopes that the reshuffle
will not affect Russia's participation in international
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Milo described the reshuffle as an internal affair of Russia,
which will not have any negative effect on Albanian-Russian ties.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the sudden reshuffle in the Russian government,
a meeting between Finnish Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen and
Chernomyrdin, scheduled to be held in northern Finland on March
27-28, has been canceled.
</P>
<P>
An alternative date for the summit will be worked out following
the formation of a new Russian government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
