BAGHDAD -- A mass funeral was held in Baghdad Tuesday for 23
Iraqi children who died due to the shortages of food and medicine
caused by the seven-year-old U.N. economic sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Participants set out from al-Shaheed Adnan Khairalla Square in
downtown Baghdad and headed toward the five-star Rasheed Hotel,
where the visiting Chairman of the U.N. Special Commission
(UNSCOM) on disarmament in Iraq, Richard Butler, and most foreign
correspondents stay. (Iraq-Children-Funeral)
