NEW DELHI -- At least 60 people were killed and 1,000 others
injured when a severe cyclone ripped through some areas in India's
West Bengal and Orissa states Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that at least 50 people were killed
and over 1,000 injured in a big tornado in West Bengal's Midnapore
district bordering Orissa state. The toll might rise as the rescue
 operation was in full swing.
</P>
<P>
At least 16 people were killed and several others injured when
a tornado hit some villages in Jaleswar of Balasore district in
Orissa state Tuesday afternoon. (India-Tornado-Death Toll)
