JOHANNESBURG -- De Beers, South African diamond giant, has
concluded a 50-50 joint-venture agreement with Russia's Soglasiye
gem miner to exploit the rich Lomonosov deposit near Arkhangelsk,
northwest Russia, a De Beers official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The venture will be the first to allow a foreign company to
mine diamonds on Russian soil, said Raymond Clarke, the Head of De
Beers in Moscow, the capital of Russia. (SAfrica-Russia-Diamond
Venture)
</P>
