<HEADLINE> Treviso Edges Efes in Men's Basketball Euro Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Benetton Treviso of Italy defeated
Turkey's Efes Istanbul 67-57 in a quarter-final first leg tie in
Treviso, Italy on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Halftime score was 36-28 in favour of the Treviso team.
</P>
<P>
The hosts opened up a 26-21 lead after 14 minutes thanks to a
superb triple from guard Henry Williams.
</P>
<P>
At the start of the second half the Turks fought back and
reduced the gap to two points (39-37) before Treviso upped their
game and opened an unassailable 10 point lead at 49-39.
</P>
<P>
Treviso's Yugoslav pivot Zeliko Rebraca was in unstoppable form
and collected 31 points.
</P>
<P>
In Bologna, Kinder Bologna of Italy beat Teamsystem Bologna
64-52 after leading 39-28 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Partizan Belgrade of Yugoslavia beat Russia's CSKA Moscow 87-72
with Belgrade leading halftime score 49-24 in Belgrade while in
Athens, AEK Athens of Greece knocked out Alba Berlin of Germany
88-68 after leading halftime score 47-27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
