<HEADLINE> Investment in Peru Represents 24.6 Percent of GDP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Investment in Peru represented 24.6
percent of the gross domestic product (GDP) in 1997, said the
central bank.
</P>
<P>
But statistics show that the investment rate has been declining
throughout last year, from 25 percent in the first three months to
24 percent in the last quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
The decline was mainly attributed to the Asian crisis, which
made it difficult to draw new investment in mining and tourism
sectors, due to the decline on mineral's international prices, the
bank said in a report.
</P>
<P>
The rate of domestic savings also fell from 20.3 percent in the
first three months to 16.9 percent in the last quarter of the
year, while public sector savings went from 6.5 percent to 1.9
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
