<HEADLINE> Gascoigne Moves to Middlesbrough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Glasgow Rangers midfielder Paul
Gascoigne joined England first division side Middlesbrough, club
official said on television on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough manager Bryan Robson confirmed that the
three-and-a-half-year deal had been reached and the native
north-east Englishman is set to return home and rejoin his old
England colleague Robson.
</P>
<P>
The Sky television said that the deal was about three million
pounds (about five million U.S. dollars), a figure that was not
confirmed by the club.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old England international has been the subject of a
transferring controversial for the past a few monthes.
</P>
<P>
Gascoigne, who moved to Rangers from Italy's Lazio in 1995-96,
played only full one games for Rangers in the last three monthes.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough are currently second in the division and heading
back up to the Premiership after being relegated last season.
</P>
</TEXT>
