<HEADLINE> China Shipping Oil Pipes To North Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- China is now sending oil and gas
pipes from the Tianjin Port to the Sudan for an oil pipeline
contract with the northern African country.
</P>
<P>
This marks the entry of Chinese-built oil pipes into the
international market.
</P>
<P>
The 1,540-kilometer pipeline is a major development project in
the Sudan and is designed to carry 11.95 million tons of crude oil
annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
