<HEADLINE> Albright, Primakov Meet in Germany on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOGNE, Germany, March 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright and her Russian counterpart, Yevgeni Primakov,
met here Tuesday evening to prepare for a Contact Group meeting in
Bonn Wednesday which will seek further measures to end the
conflict in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Without disclosing details, Primakov said after the meeting
that he expected a substantial development at the Contact Group
talks which will also be attended by foreign ministers from
Britain, France, Germany and Italy.
</P>
<P>
As a follow-up meeting to an earlier one in London on March 9,
the Contact Group talks are due to give a new assessment of the
Kosovo situation and discuss further sanctions sought by the
United States to increase pressure on President Slobodan Milosevic
of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia to begin a political
dialogue with Kosovo-Albanians on the future status of the
southern Serbian province.
</P>
<P>
Although Albright has preached for a tough stance, most other
Contact Group members, especially Russia, have been reluctant to
crack down economically or diplomatically on Belgrade at the
current stage.
</P>
<P>
However, diplomats here noted that the latest news reports
about renewed fightings in Kosovo, during which several people
were reportedly killed, would give the United States a strong
argument to push for further sanctions like seizing Serbian and
Yugoslav government assets abroad and placing restrictions on
foreign travel by Yugoslav officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
