<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks rebounded Tuesday
when the Dow Jones industrial average ended 88.19 points higher to
8,904.44, with a gap of just 1.99 points to its record close
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Transportation shares were firm amid a retreat in crude
following Monday's hike in oil prices triggered by major oil
producers' announcement to cut oil output for price stablization.
</P>
<P>
Gainers also included financial stocks amid merger rumors.
</P>
<P>
Broader market measures were stronger with the Standard &AMP;
poor's 500 stock list up 10.10 to a record 1,105.65 and the New
York Stock Exchange composite index up 4.43 to 574.97.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite up 19.93 to a record
1,812.44.
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners 1,746 to 1,190 with 537 unchanged on
the New York Stock Exchange where 605 million shares were traded,
against 628 million Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
